There are several products currently being recalled from several supermarkets. These food items should not be consumed because there is an allergy or health risk, and instead, returned to the shop they were bought from to get a full refund. Here are the following items being recalled off shelves. Pack size: 95g Batch codes: 109, 110, 111, 112, 113 Best before date: December 2026 John West Sardines in Olive Oil Pack size: 120g Batch codes: 109, 110, 111, 112, 113 Best before date: December 2026 John West has issued a food recall notice for customers, and The Food Standards Agency (FSA) has released a risk statement: "These products may contain microbiological contamination and could be unsafe to eat." "If you have bought either of the above products do not eat them. Instead, return them to the store from where they were bought for a full refund. "If you have any questions or concerns, please contact consumercontact@john-west.com." This product is stocked in several supermarkets including Tesco, Morrisons and Waitrose. READ MORE: I tried Burger & Lobster's new limited edition surf 'n' turf roll Pack size: 150g Best before dates: February 28, 2023 and March 1, 2023 The FSA’s statement said, “these products contain soya making them a possible health risk for anyone with an allergy to soya”. Again, if customers had bought the sauces, “and have an allergy to soya” they are not to eat them. "Instead, please contact the Dolmio customer care line on 0800 952 1234 (UK) or 1890 812 315 (Northern Ireland) for a full refund or return to the store for a full refund." Pack size: 140g Best before date: Feburary 7, 2023 Aldi is recalling Primula Spicy Cheese N Jalapeno because of a temperature control issue that could potentially spoil the product, which may be unsafe to eat. Customers are asked to not consume the product if they have purchased it and to return it to the store for a full refund. A full list of affected stores is available on the Aldi website at www.aldi.co.uk/products-notices DON'T MISS...Menopause: How to get rid of belly fat - best diet to follow [COMMENT]Spain: Brits left to ‘roast’ in heat as strict air con rules passed [NEWS]How Meghan portays herself as ‘innocent’ and ‘humble’ - expert claims [PICTURES] Pack size: 180g Best before dates: May 2023, June 2023, July 2023, August 2023, September 2023, and October 2023 Pack size: 400g Best before dates: May 2023, June 2023, July 2023, August 2023, September 2023, and October 2023 As for why the product is being recalled, Sainsbury’s has said there is a “possible presence of undercooked prawns” in the packs which “may make this product unsafe to eat”. Points of sale notices will be displayed in all retail stores that are selling these products, and these notices explain to customers why the products are being recalled and tell them what to do if they have bought the product. The FSA explained: “If you have bought any of the above products do not eat them. Instead, return them to the store from where they were bought for a full refund. If you have any questions or concerns, please visit Sainsbury’s website at Sainsburys.co.uk/help or contact their care line on 0800636262.” READ MORE: 18 food storage hacks to make your shopping last longer Pack size: 200g Batch code: VN394 Best before dates: All date codes up to and including June 2023 Pack size: 250g Batch code: VN394 Best before dates: All date codes up to and including February 2024 The supermarket said there is a “possible presence of raw, uncooked prawns in the products listed above”. The FSA advised: “If you have bought any of the above products do not eat them. Instead, return them to the store from where they were bought for a full refund.” Pack size: One litre Batch code: L 090 2 (the affected batch was manufactured between 15:07 and 18:24) Best before date: December 31, 2022 The FSA issued a risk statement: "This product contains oats (gluten) making it a possible health risk for anyone with an allergy or intolerance to gluten." Customers are asked to return the product to store for a full refund. "If you have any queries, please contact the Alpro Careline team on 0333 300 0900 or at https://www.alpro.com/uk/contact/." The product is sold at Sainsbury’s and Morrisons. Pack size: 465 ml Batch code: L1278 Best before date: April 2023 Ben & Jerry’s is recalling one batch of Ben & Jerry’s Moo-phoria™ Peanut Butter Cookie Dough Ice Cream sold at Sainsbury’s because the product “contains peanuts making it a possible health risk for anyone with an allergy to peanuts”. Pack size: 120g Best before: August 15, 2022, September 5, 2022 and September 26, 2022 The product “contains milk making it a possible health risk for anyone with an allergy or intolerance to milk or milk constituents”. Again, customers are asked to return the product to store for a refund. They can also contact Co-op’s Customer Careline on 0800 0686 727 or email customer.careline@coop.co.uk. Pack size: Box containing 12 x 4 packs Best before: All best before dates between February 8, 2023 to July, 11 2023 The FSA issued a risk statement: "This product contains egg making it a possible health risk for anyone with an allergy or intolerance to egg." Customers should return the item to store for a full refund.